### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@email = test@nirnayai.local
@password = Password123!
@botToken = bot-super-secret-token

### 1. Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Login to get Access Token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Capture the Access Token from Login
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
@refreshToken = {{login.response.body.refreshToken}}

### 3. Upload an APK for Analysis (Requires valid accessToken)
# Make sure to run this through an IDE extension like "REST Client" in VS Code
# and select a valid .apk file from your system.
POST {{baseUrl}}/scan/upload
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=WebAppBoundary

--WebAppBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="apk"; filename="test.apk"
Content-Type: application/vnd.android.package-archive

< ./path_to_your_malware.apk
--WebAppBoundary--

### 4. Check Scan Status
# Replace :id with the scanId returned from the upload request
@scanId = 1
GET {{baseUrl}}/scan/status/{{scanId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Get Final AI Report
GET {{baseUrl}}/scan/report/{{scanId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6. Refresh the JWT Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 7. WhatsApp Bot Upload Bypass (No JWT required, uses Bot Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/scan/bot-upload
x-bot-token: {{botToken}}
x-whatsapp-sender: 1234567890@s.whatsapp.net
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=BotBoundary

--BotBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="apk"; filename="test.apk"
Content-Type: application/vnd.android.package-archive

< ./path_to_your_malware.apk
--BotBoundary--
